<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Currently you can't specify what type of message you're sending with the FlashMessenger in Zend_Controller. It's just a message.</p>

<p>I would like to be able to differentiate the messages I'm sending via FlashMessenger (e.g. error, warning, information, tip, etc.) so users can see more clearly what's going on. Therefore I propose to enhance the addMessage method of the FlashMessenger with an additional argument that allows setting the type of message.</p>

<p>Change:
addMessage (string $message, string $namespace)</p>

<p>To:
addMessage (string $message, string $message_type, string $namespace)</p>

    </div>
